                "role": "assistant",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "data": "All files are in place. Here's a summary of everything created:\n\n---\n\n## What was created\n\n```\nnetwork-topology/\n├── index.html              # HTML shell with HUD, legend, and controls hint\n├── package.json            # three@0.169.0, vite@5.4.11, typescript@5.6.3\n├── tsconfig.json           # strict mode, ESNext modules, bundler resolution\n├── vite.config.ts          # Vite bundler config\n├── README.md               # Full setup guide (see below)\n└── src/\n    ├── main.ts             # Scene, lighting, demo graph, animation loop, raycasting\n    ├── NetworkGraph.ts     # Graph manager — addNode / addLink / update\n    ├── NetworkNode.ts      # Node class — 4 types, 3 statuses, label sprites\n    ├── NetworkLink.ts      # Edge class — animated line, 3 link statuses\n    ├── Tooltip.ts          # Hover tooltip DOM element\n    └── style.css           # Dark-theme HUD, legend panel, controls hint\n```\n\n### Demo topology included\n12 nodes (2 routers → 3 switches → 2 servers + 5 clients) with varied statuses and link types, floating animation, and a pulsing point light.\n\n### To run (from a WSL or Linux terminal)\n\n```bash\ncd network-topology\nnpm install\nnpm run dev\n# open http://localhost:5173\n```\n\n> The one gotcha: since your project is in the WSL filesystem, **npm must be run from a WSL terminal** (Ubuntu, Debian, etc.), not from Windows CMD/PowerShell. The README documents this in both the setup steps and the troubleshooting table."
                  }
                ],
