                "content": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "data": "You're running `npm install` from the parent directory `Simulador_topologia_red` instead of the project subdirectory. The `package.json` is inside `network-topology/`.\n\nFrom your Windows terminal, navigate one level deeper:\n\n```cmd\ncd network-topology\nnpm install\n```\n\nOr if you're already in `Simulador_topologia_red`:\n\n```cmd\ncd network-topology\nnpm install\nnpm run dev\n```\n\nThe full path you need to be in is:\n```\n\\\\wsl.localhost\\Ubuntu-24.04\\home\\jose\\Simulador_topologia_red\\network-topology\n```\n\nThat said, you'll still hit the UNC path esbuild error I mentioned. The most reliable fix is to run everything from a **WSL terminal** instead:\n\n1. Open **Ubuntu** (or whichever WSL distro you have) from the Start menu\n2. Then run:\n```bash\ncd ~/Simulador_topologia_red/network-topology\nnpm install\nnpm run dev\n```\n\nThis avoids the Windows CMD UNC path limitation entirely."
                  }
                ],
                "meta": {
                  "timestamp": 1783331034
