                "role": "assistant",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "data": "Done. Here's what changed in the README:\n\n- **Features** — added bullet about editable parameters, live feature updates, n-dimensional Mesh/Torus, and the rebuild button.\n- **Topologies** — each topology section now has two tables: one for its **editable parameters** (key, description, default, range) and one for its **computed properties** showing which formula drives each value.\n- **Project Structure** — updated descriptions for `TopologyInfo.ts`, `topologies.ts`, and `topologyMeta.ts` to reflect the new param-driven design.\n- **Controls** — added rows for editing parameters, live feature updates, and the rebuild action.\n- **Adding a New Topology** — completely rewritten to cover the new `paramFields`, `defaultParams`, `computeFeatures`, and `generate(params)` API, with a field types reference table.\n- **Architecture Overview** — updated to show `TopologyInfo(onRebuild)`, the live `computeFeatures()` call on input, `buildGraph(id, params)`, and the submit → rebuild flow.\n- **Troubleshooting** — added a row for when the graph is too large/overlapping (reduce params in UI)."
                  }
                ],
                "meta": {
                  "timestamp": 1783333404
                }
              }
            },
