              "rand": 908070701
            },
            "result": {
              "Ok": {
                "id": "831b61b6-2013-440b-b822-a476f590a5e4",
                "role": "assistant",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "data": "Done. Here's what changed and why it fixes the problem:\n\n**Root cause:** `THREE.LineBasicMaterial` renders all lines as exactly 1px regardless of the `linewidth` setting — a WebGL limitation. In dense topologies, coplanar lines connecting the same node pairs overlap into a single undistinguishable pixel.\n\n**What was changed:**\n\n- **`NetworkLink.ts`** — replaced `THREE.Line` + `LineBasicMaterial` with `THREE.TubeGeometry` + `MeshPhongMaterial`. Links are now real 3D cylinders with volume, shading, and depth — they never visually overlap because they occupy actual space in the scene.\n\n- **`topologies.ts` — Torus** — wrap-around links now get:\n  - An `arc` value proportional to the grid size, which bows them upward in an arc above the grid plane, making them clearly visible as the \"circular\" connections they represent.\n  - A distinct color per dimension (red for X-wraps, violet for Y-wraps, teal for Z-wraps).\n\n- **`topologies.ts` — Flattened Butterfly** — all-to-all links now get:\n  - Row links (horizontal): arced **upward (Y+)**, amber color. Arc height scales with the hop distance so non-adjacent pairs rise higher and don't cover adjacent ones.\n  - Column links (vertical): arced **forward (Z+)**, violet color. This separates them from row arcs in a different axis, making both sets independently readable.\n\n- **`topologies.ts`** — `LinkDef` got two new optional fields: `arc` (fraction of link length) and `color` (hex override).\n- **`NetworkGraph.ts`** and **`main.ts`** — forward those fields through to `NetworkLink`."
                  }
                ],
                "meta": {
                  "timestamp": 1783334018
                }
              }
            },
