                    "path": "network-topology/README.md",
                    "content": "# Network Topology Visualizer\n\nAn interactive 3D network topology viewer built with **Three.js** and **TypeScript**, bundled by **Vite**.\n\n![screenshot placeholder](docs/screenshot.png)\n\n---\n\n## Features\n\n- 3D scene with orbit controls (rotate, zoom, pan)\n- Four node types: **Router**, **Switch**, **Server**, **Client** — each with a distinct geometry and color\n- Three link statuses: **Active** (cyan), **Saturated** (red), **Inactive** (grey)\n- Three node statuses: **Online**, **Offline**, **Warning** (reflected via emissive color)\n- Hover tooltip showing node id, type, and status\n- Animated nodes (gentle float + router spin) and pulsing ambient light\n- HUD title, legend panel, and controls hint overlay\n\n---\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n| Tool | Minimum version |\n|------|----------------|\n| Node.js | 18.x or later |\n| npm | 9.x or later (bundled with Node 18) |\n\n> Verify with `node -v` and `npm -v`.\n\n---\n\n## Project Structure\n\n```\nnetwork-topology/\n├── index.html              # HTML entry point\n├── package.json            # Dependencies and npm scripts\n├── tsconfig.json           # TypeScript compiler options\n├── vite.config.ts          # Vite bundler config\n└── src/\n    ├── main.ts             # Scene bootstrap, lighting, demo graph, animation loop\n    ├── NetworkGraph.ts     # Graph manager (add nodes & links)\n    ├── NetworkNode.ts      # Node class + geometry/material per type\n    ├── NetworkLink.ts      # Link/edge class\n    ├── Tooltip.ts          # Hover tooltip UI\n    └── style.css           # HUD and overlay styles\n```\n\n---\n\n## Setup & Running\n\n### 1. Clone or download the project\n\n```bash\ngit clone <repo-url>\ncd network-topology\n```\n\nOr simply navigate to the directory if you already have the files:\n\n```bash\ncd network-topology\n```\n\n### 2. Install dependencies\n\n```bash\nnpm install\n```\n\nThis installs:\n- `three` — 3D rendering engine\n- `vite` — fast dev server and bundler\n- `typescript` — type-checker\n- `@types/three` — Three.js type definitions\n\n### 3. Start the development server\n\n```bash\nnpm run dev\n```\n\nVite will print a local URL (usually `http://localhost:5173`). Open it in any modern browser.\n\n### 4. (Optional) Build for production\n\n```bash\nnpm run build\n```\n\nThe optimised output is written to `dist/`. Serve it with any static file host:\n\n```bash\nnpm run preview   # preview the production build locally\n```\n\n---\n\n## Controls\n\n| Action | Input |\n|--------|-------|\n| Rotate scene | Left-click + drag |\n| Zoom | Mouse wheel |\n| Pan | Right-click + drag |\n| Node info | Hover over a node |\n\n---\n\n## Customising the Topology\n\nAll nodes and links are defined in `src/main.ts`. Use the `NetworkGraph` API:\n\n### Adding a node\n\n```ts\ngraph.addNode({\n  id: 'myNode',          // unique string id\n  label: 'My Node',      // display label\n  type: 'router',        // 'router' | 'switch' | 'server' | 'client'\n  status: 'online',      // 'online' | 'offline' | 'warning'  (optional, default: 'online')\n  position: { x: 0, y: 0, z: 0 },  // world-space position (optional)\n})\n```\n\n### Adding a link\n\n```ts\ngraph.addLink({\n  sourceId: 'myNode',\n  targetId: 'anotherNode',\n  bandwidth: 1000,        // Mbps — informational only (optional)\n  status: 'active',       // 'active' | 'inactive' | 'saturated'  (optional)\n})\n```\n\n### Changing node / link status at runtime\n\n```ts\nconst node = graph.getNode('myNode')\nnode?.setStatus('warning')\n\n// Links are returned by addLink:\nconst link = graph.addLink({ ... })\nlink?.setStatus('saturated')\n```\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\n```\nmain.ts\n  ├─ creates THREE.Scene, Camera, WebGLRenderer\n  ├─ adds lighting (AmbientLight, DirectionalLight, PointLight)\n  ├─ instantiates NetworkGraph(scene)\n  │     ├─ NetworkGraph  — owns the Map<id, NetworkNode> and NetworkLink[]\n  │     ├─ NetworkNode   — wraps a THREE.Mesh + label Sprite; exposes setStatus()\n  │     └─ NetworkLink   — wraps a THREE.Line; updates geometry every frame\n  ├─ instantiates Tooltip — creates a fixed <div> for hover info\n  ├─ sets up Raycaster for mouse picking\n  └─ runs the animation loop (requestAnimationFrame)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n| Symptom | Fix |\n|---------|-----|\n| Blank screen | Check browser console for errors; ensure `npm install` was run |\n| `Cannot find module 'three/addons/...'` | Run `npm install` — `@types/three` must be installed |\n| TypeScript errors on `build` | Run `npm run dev` first to confirm the runtime works, then review type errors |\n| Very low FPS | Reduce `devicePixelRatio` in `main.ts` or lower shadow map size |\n\n---\n\n## License\n\nMIT\n"
                  }
