      "version": "v1",
      "kind": "AssistantMessage",
      "data": {
        "message_id": "6b098073-fdb8-47d4-93d8-e244a0f168b5",
        "content": [
          {
            "kind": "text",
            "data": "All done. Here's what was implemented:\n\n---\n\n## What was added\n\n### Parameter controls — how it works\n\nEach topology in the right panel now shows a **Parámetros** form above the features table:\n\n| Topology | Parameters |\n|---|---|\n| **Mesh** | `n` (dimensions), `k` (n-tuple of switches per dimension), `m` (endpoint nodes per switch) |\n| **Torus** | Same as Mesh (`n`, `k`, `m`) |\n| **WK-Recursiva** | `k` (clique size), `l` (expansion level, 1–3) |\n| **Fat Tree** | `k` (branching factor), `n` (number of stages) |\n| **Flattened Butterfly** | `p` (rows), `q` (columns) |\n| **Bus** | `nodeCount` (number of nodes) |\n\n**Behaviour:**\n- Changing any value in the form **immediately updates the features table** (no rebuild needed).\n- Clicking **↺ Reconstruir** (or pressing Enter) regenerates the full 3D graph with the new parameters.\n- The `k` tuple for Mesh/Torus automatically pads or trims to match the current `n` value.\n- All inputs are clamped to safe ranges to prevent exponential blowups.\n- The Mesh and Torus generators are now truly **n-dimensional** — set `n=3` and you'll get a 3D grid; `n=1` gives a chain."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "version": "v1",
