    {
      "version": "v1",
      "kind": "AssistantMessage",
      "data": {
        "message_id": "b806b0b1-3dcb-4833-a0df-cb6c5ee656ed",
        "content": [
          {
            "kind": "text",
            "data": "Now I have a clear picture. The issue is twofold:\n\n1. **Torus**: wrap-around links go from the last switch in a row/column directly back to the first — they overlap exactly with the regular mesh links and are invisible.\n2. **Flattened Butterfly**: all-to-all connections within rows and columns produce many lines between adjacent nodes, all coplanar and overlapping.\n\nThe solution is:\n- Replace `THREE.Line` with **tube meshes** (real 3D cylinders) so lines have actual visual thickness.\n- Add a **`arc` parameter** to `LinkDef` so generators can flag certain links (wrap-arounds, dense all-to-all) to be rendered with a curved arc instead of a straight line, lifting them out of the plane of the nodes."
          },
          {
            "kind": "toolUse",
            "data": {
              "toolUseId": "tooluse_7w6Mk4obs3i6BMnkCSvzr9",
              "name": "todo_list",
              "input": {
                "__tool_use_purpose": "Creating task list for link visibility improvements",
                "command": "create",
                "task_list_description": "Fix link visibility in Torus and Flattened Butterfly: replace Line with tube meshes, add arc support for wrap-around and dense links",
                "tasks": [
                  {
                    "task_description": "Add arc/color metadata to LinkDef; update torus wrap-around and butterfly links to use arcs and distinct colors"
                  },
                  {
                    "task_description": "Rewrite NetworkLink to render tubes (TubeGeometry) with arc support instead of flat lines"
                  },
                  {
                    "task_description": "Update NetworkGraph.addLink to pass arc/color through to NetworkLink"
                  },
                  {
                    "task_description": "Run tsc and fix any type errors"
                  }
                ]
              }
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "version": "v1",
      "kind": "ToolResults",
      "data": {
        "message_id": "15d639a6-1727-4801-ad90-70a589846b40",
        "content": [
          {
